Ed Murphy wrote:
>Proto-Proposal:  Plots (v3.2)
>
>100 Structures and 10,000 Ergs are created in the Bank's possession.

Is there much point creating 10,000 Ergs? The Chancellor can mint them
as required.

>Amend Rule 1677 ("Currency Awards for New Players") to read:
>
>      As soon as possible after the start of a Player's Grace Period, the
>      Registrar shall pay out 5 Voting Tokens, 5 P-Notes, and 15 Ergs to that
>      Player.  In addition, the Registrar shall report to the Cartographor that
>      3 Structures are created in that Player's possession.
>
>Amend Rule 1701 ("Proposal Notes") by removing this paragraph:
>
>      Whenever there exists a Player who has never before possessed
>      any P-Notes, the Promotor shall pay out 5 P-Notes to that Player.
>
>Create a Rule with this text:
>
>      Upon the creation of this Rule:
>        * All Voting Tokens and P-Notes are destroyed.
>        * All obligations to transfer Currency are cancelled.
>        * For each Player, 5 VTs, 5 P-Notes, 15 Ergs, and 3 Structures are
>            created in that Player's possession.
>
>      One second after this Rule is created, it repeals itself.

5 P-notes is too many, in both cases. Players don't make Proposals nearly
as often as they vote. By giving every Player 5 P-Notes, you're effectively
creating the opportunity to make 80 Proposals for free. It'd be a long
time before we saw P-Note scarcity after that. I'd recommend changing
it to 1 P-Note.

>[Part Three:  Make Structures useful]
>
>Create a rule titled "Maintenance of Structures" with this text:
>
>      At the beginning of the month, each Player's Maintenance Fee for that
>      month becomes due.  One week after the beginning of the month, each
>      Player's Maintenance Fee for that month becomes delinquent, unless it has
>      already been paid.
>
>      A Player's Maintenance Fee equals the total of the Maintenance Fees of
>      all the Structures e owns, plus 1 Erg per Type of Structure e owns.  This
>      value is fixed at the time the Fee becomes due.
>
>      A Player's Maintenance Fee for a given month is paid when e successfully
>      pays that amount to the Bank for the sole purpose of paying eir
>      Maintenance Fee for that month.
>
>      As soon as possible after a Player's Maintenance Fee becomes due, the
>      Cartographor shall inform that Player of the amount of the Fee.
>
>      As soon as possible after a Player's Maintenance Fee becomes delinquent,
>      the Cartographor shall report that all Structures owned by that Player
>      are destroyed.

This doesn't use the PC structures for handling Currency transactions.
Why not? As you have it, Players are incurring obligations to pay Fees
automagically at the beginning of the month, without seeing a message
informing them that they have incurred this obligation. This is Bad,
the kind of Bad we introduced PC to avoid. Also, the Cartographor can
wait nearly the whole week before reporting Fees, leaving hours or
possibly only minutes before the Fees thus reported become
delinquent. Is this fair? If Players expected to keep track of their
own Maintenance Fees, why have the Cartographor keep track of them?
If the Rule were made PC-compliant, this problem wouldn't arise: no
Player would incur an obligation to pay a Maintenance Fee until
the Cartographor had reported it by executing a PO for Ergs, and no
Fee could become delinquent until a week after that.

One last question: am I right or wrong in assuming that Structures are
limited to one per Plot? Can you point me to the part of the proto where
this is specified?
