Charles E. Carroll wrote:
>
>Steve Gardner wrote:
>>
>>I take the opposite tack. I think it's pretty clearly truly hideous,
>>but I worry about whether it's a really a pun, or actually a distinct
>>species of wordplay, eg a spoonerism.
>
>I don't think the two are mutually exclusive.

Having checked the Complete OED, I think I agree with you. For 'pun'
it gives, inter alia:

pun, sb. The use of a word in such a way as to suggest two or more
meanings or associations, or the use of two or more words with
the same or nearly the same sound with different meanings, so as to
produce a humourous effect.

With that definition in front of me, I'd have to say that Crito's
Proposal did contain a pun. Of course, that still may not be enough
to satisfy the Silly Proposal Rules.

